Malicious usb cable, flash drive or any kind of hardware (even keyboard and mouse) - looks like a normal usb but it has additional electronics inside. 
Computer can recognize it as a keyboard or mouse. It can install various malicious softwares

Skimming - stealing credit card infromation, usually during normal transaction. Copying data from magnetic stripe.
This can happen during ATM transaction. Attacker can instal little camera or modify PIN pad to gather you PIN number.